HEADWORD: Monotocous
<hw>Mo*not"o*cous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + Gr. <?/ birth, offspring.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bearing fruit but once; monocarpic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Uniparous; laying a single
egg.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monotomous</ent>⟦br⟧
